        "Calculate 70.90/64.06 = 1.1066 ≈ 1.107, confirming Cl2/SO2",
        "Record photochemical equation: SO2(g) + Cl2(g) → SO2Cl2(l) under hν"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Apply SO2Cl2+2H2O→H2SO4+2HCl to verify 2:1 strong-acid ratio and BaSO4 precipitate",
      "atomics": [
        "Balance hydrolysis: SO2Cl2 + 2H2O → H2SO4 + 2HCl; count 2 mol HCl per 1 mol H2SO4",
        "Classify H2SO4 and HCl as strong acids satisfying the problem constraint",
        "Write ionic equation BaCl2 + H2SO4 → BaSO4↓ + 2HCl, assign C=BaSO4"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Compute M(Y)=134.97/1.134=119.0 g/mol and match to SOCl2 (thionyl chloride, 118.97 g/mol)",
      "atomics": [
        "Divide M(SO2Cl2)=134.97 by 1.134 to get 119.0 g/mol",
        "Check S+O+Cl2=32+16+71=119 g/mol for SOCl2, confirming same-element liquid Y",
        "Verify back-ratio 134.97/118.97=1.1345≈1.134"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": [
    "Confirm M(SO2Cl2)=32+32+(2×35.5)=135 g/mol and literature confirmation as fuming poisonous liquid",
    "Cross-check all five problem constraints simultaneously against SO2Cl2 to rule out alternative structures"
